feature: latency_slo_routing
description: >
  Routes latency SLO breach alerts to appropriate notification channels
  (PagerDuty, Slack, or Database log) depending on the alert severity.
business_logic:
  - Consumes alerts.latency.slo topic.
  - severity='page': Suppresses duplicate pages for the same (model, endpoint) within 15 minutes using Redis. Triggers high-priority PagerDuty incident if not suppressed.
  - severity='slack': Sends detailed SLO breach alert containing burn rate trends to #llm-latency-alerts channel.
  - severity='ticket': Inserts alert records into the PostgreSQL alert_history database table.
dependencies:
  - Redis (for deduplication / rate-limiting)
  - PagerDuty API / Client
  - Slack Client / Webhook
  - PostgreSQL Database (for historical audit logs)
criticality: High
networking:
  - Outbound Slack Webhook calls
  - Outbound PagerDuty Events API v2 calls
  - Inbound Redis queries for rate-limiting
  - Inbound PostgreSQL connections for inserts
